description: Public radio station RFI says a "technical problem" meant the obituaries were published prematurely.
title: Radio France Internationale publishes obituaries of people still alive
title_page: Radio France Internationale publishes obituaries of people still alive - BBC News
maintext: French businessman Bernie Tapie, 77, who was on the list of people who had their death notice published by RFI, has had his obituary published on at least two other occasions by other news outlets.
